<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-01-0649 </DOCNO><TEXT>Following the public inquiry into the building of a PWR type reactor atSizewell in Suffolk, the Inquiry Inspector, Sir Frank Layfield, has issuedhis report. It recommends that the PWR is built. However, the actualdecision rests with the Secretary of State for Energy, but there willbe a parliamentary debate first. The key recommendations of the Layfieldreport are given. The future of nuclear power in the UK is reviewed assumingthat the Sizewell-B PWR project is allowed to proceed. The commercialreactors now in operation are listed and an estimate of future nuclearpower generation made.</TEXT></DOC>